The paper discusses the landscape of online social networks and the heterogeneous information generated by users' social activities in multiple aligned social networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Databases (cs.DB), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it covers network alignment, link prediction, community detection, information diffusion, and network embedding.
